---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import HubCard from '../../../components/HubCard.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
    title="Team Governance"
    description="Team conventions and governance for scalable CSS systems."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Teams</p>
        <p class="summary-badge">Summary Page</p>

        <h1>
            Team governance
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            Large CSS systems fail without shared architectural standards.
        </p>

        <p class="summary-note">
            This page is a summary. For full governance guidance, use
            <a href="/teams/governance/">Governance</a>.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <ul>
            <li>clear naming rules</li>
            <li>layer ownership</li>
            <li>PR review expectations</li>
            <li>migration strategy</li>
            <li>linting standards</li>
            <li>architecture documentation</li>
            <li>component ownership</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <p>
            CSS architecture should be treated as an engineering concern rather
            than a collection of isolated styling decisions.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>Next useful pages</h2>
        <div class="hub-grid">
            <HubCard href="/teams/governance/" title="Governance guide">
                <p>Use full governance principles, health checks, and failure signals.</p>
            </HubCard>
            <HubCard href="/teams/contributing/" title="Contribution standards">
                <p>Translate governance into pull request and review behavior.</p>
            </HubCard>
            <HubCard href="/teams/adoption/" title="Adoption">
                <p>Start team rollout in a way governance can sustain.</p>
            </HubCard>
        </div>
    </section>
</DocsLayout>
